#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.51"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.51:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.51:0.2"
msgid "6. Brāhmaṇavagga "
msgstr "6. Brahmins "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.51:0.3"
msgid "51. Paṭhamadvebrāhmaṇasutta "
msgstr "51. Two Brahmins (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.51:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho dve brāhmaṇā jiṇṇā vuddhā mahallakā addhagatā vayoanuppattā vīsavassasatikā jātiyā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu. "
msgstr "Then two old brahmins—elderly and senior, who were advanced in years and had reached the final stage of life, a hundred and twenty years old—went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "an3.51:1.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te brāhmaṇā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side, and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.51:1.3"
msgid "“mayamassu, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā jiṇṇā vuddhā mahallakā addhagatā vayoanuppattā vīsavassasatikā jātiyā; "
msgstr "“We brahmins, Master Gotama, are old, elderly and senior, we’re advanced in years and have reached the final stage of life; we’re a hundred and twenty years old. "

msgctxt "an3.51:1.4"
msgid "te camhā akatakalyāṇā akatakusalā akatabhīruttāṇā. "
msgstr "And we haven’t done what is good and skillful, nor have we made a shelter from fear. "

msgctxt "an3.51:1.5"
msgid "Ovadatu no bhavaṃ gotamo, anusāsatu no bhavaṃ gotamo yaṃ amhākaṃ assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Advise us, Master Gotama, instruct us! It will be for our lasting welfare and happiness.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an3.51:2.1"
msgid "“Taggha tumhe, brāhmaṇā, jiṇṇā vuddhā mahallakā addhagatā vayoanuppattā vīsavassasatikā jātiyā; "
msgstr "“Indeed, brahmins, you’re old, elderly and senior. "

msgctxt "an3.51:2.2"
msgid "te cattha akatakalyāṇā akatakusalā akatabhīruttāṇā. "
msgstr "And you haven’t done what is good and skillful, nor have you made a shelter from fear. "

msgctxt "an3.51:2.3"
msgid "Upanīyati kho ayaṃ, brāhmaṇā, loko jarāya byādhinā maraṇena. "
msgstr "This world is led on by old age, sickness, and death. "

# NOTE: BB has “support” for parayana. It does indeed mean that at AN 3.36, etc. But here it must be a synonym of the other terms.
msgctxt "an3.51:2.4"
msgid "Evaṃ upanīyamāne kho, brāhmaṇā, loke jarāya byādhinā maraṇena, yo idha kāyena saṃyamo vācāya saṃyamo manasā saṃyamo, taṃ tassa petassa tāṇañca leṇañca dīpañca saraṇañca parāyaṇañcāti. "
msgstr "But restraint here by way of body, speech, and mind is the shelter, protection, island, refuge, and haven for the departed. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.51:3.1"
msgid "Upanīyati jīvitamappamāyu, "
msgstr "This life, so very short, is led onward. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.51:3.2"
msgid "Jarūpanītassa na santi tāṇā; "
msgstr "There’s no shelter for someone who’s been led on by old age. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.51:3.3"
msgid "Etaṃ bhayaṃ maraṇe pekkhamāno, "
msgstr "Seeing this peril in death, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.51:3.4"
msgid "Puññāni kayirātha sukhāvahāni. "
msgstr "you should do good deeds that bring happiness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an3.51:4.1"
msgid "Yodha kāyena saṃyamo, "
msgstr "The restraint practiced here—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.51:4.2"
msgid "Vācāya uda cetasā; "
msgstr "of body, speech, and mind—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.51:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ tassa petassa sukhāya hoti, "
msgstr "leads the departed to happiness, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.51:4.4"
msgid "Yaṃ jīvamāno pakaroti puññan”ti. "
msgstr "as the good deeds done while living.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.51:4.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
